## Quick Start Checklist

- [ ] Pick your language (Python for easiest start, Rust for speed)
- [ ] Implement math functions first (exp, log, sqrt) — test them!
- [ ] Build the PRNG — verify distribution looks uniform
- [ ] Write matrix operations — test with known multiplications
- [ ] Build a single Layer — test forward pass
- [ ] Stack layers into a NeuralNetwork — test shapes match
- [ ] Implement backprop — test on XOR problem first
- [ ] Add the JSON parser — test with complex nested objects
- [ ] Build the MemoryManager — test read/write/delete/wipe
- [ ] Wire up the main loop — it should boot, load memory, accept input
- [ ] Train on tiny data — verify loss goes down
- [ ] Scale up and iterate

---

> **Remember:** This is a learning exercise. A 10k-line from-scratch AI won't compete with GPT, but you'll understand every single byte of how neural networks, memory systems, and inference engines actually work. That knowledge is permanent.
